    deliveryMethod: "cwc",
    preview: "A 134-year wait is not a queue; it is a life sentence in a backlog. We are asking the world’s most talented professionals to move here, build businesses, and raise families, all while knowing the curr",
    messageBody: "A 134-year wait is not a queue; it is a life sentence in a backlog. We are asking the world’s most talented professionals to move here, build businesses, and raise families, all while knowing the current statutory country caps mean many will likely die before their application is even reviewed [1]. \n\n[Personal Connection]\n\nThis level of dysfunction is a policy choice, not a necessity. Your own agency data confirms the system is failing to keep pace with reality, as USCIS reached the H-2B statutory cap for the entire second half of fiscal year 2026 by March 10th—just ten days into the period [3]. When we project wait times that span over a century for Indian H-1B holders due to the 7% per-country limit, we are effectively telling the people our economy needs most that they will never truly belong here [1].\n\nThere is a clear path forward that has already earned the support of the U.S. Chamber of Commerce and bipartisan leadership. The Dignity Act of 2025 is designed to modernize these failing pathways and address the workforce shortages that these backlogs exacerbate [2].\n\nI am asking you to use your administrative and oversight authority to champion the elimination of the per-country caps and support the immediate reforms proposed in the Dignity Act. We need an immigration system that functions on a human timeline, not a centennial one.\n\n[Name]",
